<Text>After moving to Tracy, I sustained an injury that required me to wear a foot brace that caused my lower back to be misaligned. I was suffering from lower back pain, which also resulted in knee swelling and pain.

I contacted my former Chiropractor, and he Recommended Dr. Ringer.

I have yet to be disappointed by his staff or the care I have received. The staff requested my insurance information and immediately gathered my coverage information.  I was informed of my coverage and my required co-pay. When I had to move under my husband's insurance, his staff immediately checked my coverage and informed me at my next visit of my modified coverage.

Dr. Ringer was thorough in his initial assessment, and was able to develop a treatment plan that included in-office adjustments as well as home exercises that would help strengthen my lower back and adjoining muscles. My lower back pain improved significantly and my knee swelling quickly subsided.

Dr. Ringer has treated me through two pregnancies. I had had a lot of hip and pelvic pain with both my pregnancies and he was able to treat me to help alleviate this significantly. This allowed me to sit and sleep more comfortably.

His staff is always kind and courteous to me and both of my children. They remember my kids and always greet them by name. My oldest daughter will rarely let me go alone as she enjoys visiting with them as well as getting a lollipop for being well behaved at the office.

I highly recommend Dr. Ringer for your Chiropractic needs.

Thanks Dr. Ringer!</Text>< name>

< review>
As I climbed into my bed a interesting pain in my lower back. I knew something was wrong instantly. I tried to stand up and collapsed on the floor. My wife couldn't help me up because I am over 200 pounds. But she did something better for me! After finding my old cane she handed me pain killer and made an apointment at her chiropractor Dr. Ringer's office in Tracy.

We scheduled the apointment for 5:30 pm. I managed to get into the car and to the doctors office to be seen.

With in minutes of the visit I was already in a room waiting for the chiropractor. He was able to identify the issue quickly and with in a couple minutes he did an adjustment and I was albe to walk again!

I spent the next couple days using my cane as we did follow up visits.

< Review>
We have been to Longbranch and Paisan (now operating as a single entity) several times before Covid closed indoor dining, and twice since then. This review is mostly for the post-Covid setup but is similar to our prior experiences.
As takeout, their food is good, but not worth their prices.
The outdoor-dining experience is not good: it‚Äôs basically takeout on picnic tables, with plastic silverware and no service. The most recent time, the food was barely warm - the fried cheese curds were at room temperature and the lasagna similarly seemed like it had just been re-heated after a long time out.
Their cocktails, before and now, are mediocre.
Before covid, their service was inconsistent.
I hope they improve their in-person dining experience, outdoors and soon indoors again.</Review>

1576557874097</Time>
< Rating>
4< /Rating>
< review>
Solid place for a good cocktail, though you'll pay for it. Beer selection is pretty extensive, but hadn't changed as much over time as I would expect. I'm in to darker beers (ales specifically) and was able to taste their selection in a single flight.

Service for food was fine, but I wish they would have more options for finger food on their menu. If I come here I am looking for drinks with some food to munch, not a full risotto plate. That being said, this place advertises as a bar/saloon so I am not going to be too critical on the menu.

A couple times I went in and thought they closed really early. Had a quick drink and ended up going elsewhere for a snack.

Parking can be a pain during busy hours, particularly with the construction on the South West corner of Dwight and San Pablo.< /review>

< Text>
We went there twice recently and determined it's not a regular spot for us.  The drinks (cocktails and wine/beer selection) and atmosphere are definitely worth it.  Though the food can be tasty but really heavy.  4 of us ordered quite a few different items - even our daughter found Bruschetta too oily and heavy and didn't finish.  For the price, they can certainly use better ingredients.
The service is so tentative and aloof.  Seems totally lacking any kind of training and expectations from the management.
Go for the drinks, cheese curds and atmosphere.  There are better options for food and dining.<//Text>

I've wondered about this place as I've driven by several times, so I parked my Harley, went and checked the door and it wasn't locked, I saw no sign indicating it wasn't open, so I put money in the meter and walked right in after seeing several people sitting around.

Great Service. Food is wonderful.</Text>
<Time>1496153646473< /Time><pics>None<//pics>< user>
104212699827645796388</user>
<Rating>5<//Rating><GmapID>0x80857eed6b1d1d33:0x679dc1eb943beaf< /GmapID></record>

<review>a bit shocking this place has no reviews. Although some might scoff at the oh-so-trendy menu, interior, beers, you should agree that west berkeley needs something like this. It's away from the student crush, catering to Pixar people and startups in the cheaper part of berkeley.

Food is excellent. The fried cheese curds were a squeeky treat. The ribs were seriously honest fatty delights.

The beer list is exceptional, with about 15 taps, and plenty of small local beers that I haven't seen. They're highlighting microbrewers from alameda and berekely. Their idea of a "large" brewer would be Drake and Lagunitas, but they have the less available beers of those.

Parking is also simple. Compares very favorably to Box and Bells, similar concept, lower cost, better food (really).

And the kitchen is open late --- we came in at 11pm on a friday and although they were closing up (midnight close time) they happily served us.< /review>< pics>
None< /pics>

<Time>1445189227954</Time><text>Set up agreement noon on Saturday. Dealt with Cindy Chaisson, the assistant manager. It was stated that I'd lock the unit later, as I was in a rush. No indication made from Cindy that a lock was on the unit or that I needed to have someone escort me to the unit to unlock it during office hours. She also never took the initiative to take my lock and place it on the unit for me, only put a sticker on it. Arrived Saturday after office hours to come lock my unit, approximately 9pm, to discover the unit was locked. That evening I attempted to contact emergency help line, only to be directed to call Sunday morning at 7am. I was moving and packing stuff til 2:30am. So now I had to wake up extra early for this phone call. I contact the number provided at 7am, to be told Cindy nor her assistant could be reached, and that a voicemail was left, and to follow up in half an hour again if I don't receive a call back. I received no call back. I called customer support again at 750am (as call log states - originally I thought this call was 742am), and support was able to reach Cindy. Cindy stated to the representative she needed 15 minutes (810am). I leave to arrive on-site in 10 minutes (805am). I wait 10 minutes in front of the office, til 815am, with no arrival from Cindy. I then called support once again to receive an ETA. They reached her and I was told 10 minutes, but potentially longer. I waited until 845 with no arrival from Cindy. I then called back again to support to find out where she is now, for which they state, she already unlocked the unit!!!!!! No phone call made by her to tell me she arrived or unlocked the unit! So I was essentially on the hook to wait there all day unless I called back to support.

Overall, these kinds of decisions and lack of professionalism make me never wish to use Extra Space Storage again, after the trial month is over, given the type of service I can expect at the management level. I hope others also avoid this headache. I've used other providers and never had an issue. The only reason this place was used was location was next door to our apartment complex. < review>
I cannot believe the hype around this place. Went here because I needed a quick bite. I‚Äôm quite fond of Vietnamese food so I like seeing what different places have to offer and this place was very disappointing. A one star is extreme but I‚Äôve read and seen the other reviews on here and yelp and I just can‚Äôt believe them. At the very least this place is not representative of ‚Äúinexpensive‚Äù or ‚ÄúVietnamese‚Äù food.  I don‚Äôt know why this place is listed as cheap because it‚Äôs a rip-off compared to other restaurants that serve the same food in the same area.

My grips:

Bahn Mi Sandwich
- Their small is priced what most places charge normally and their ‚Äúlarge‚Äù is $2 more and is the size of most place‚Äôs regular size.

- There was less meat on the large than what I get on most place‚Äôs regular sized and cheaper sandwiches.  I‚Äôd say vegetarians should consider this place if you‚Äôre worried about getting meat on your sandwich because you won‚Äôt.

- ‚ÄúLarge‚Äù means ‚Äúmore bread‚Äù.

- Someone there must own a pepper farm because these people seem to think spicy peppers should be used as a filler instead of a garnish.

Vietnamese Iced Coffee

- Same ‚Äúsmall‚Äù and ‚Äúlarge‚Äù problems as the sandwich.

- 3/4 of the drink was thick cubed ice.

- The server initially gave me a small even though I asked and paid for a large.  I corrected him and watched him remake the next one. He just poured the small into a large cup, and added a few more ice cubes.

-  The server asked me before making the drink (in the wrong size) if I wanted it sweet.  I said yes. The drink was more bitter than a Starbucks cold stale straight black brew.

I‚Äôm not a foodie and I don‚Äôt normally care enough about poor restaurant experience to say anything. I just don‚Äôt go back. Obviously this place inspired me to react this way. That‚Äôs not a motivator I‚Äôd like associated with my Vietnamese restaurant of choice.<//review>

My husband and I moved in here three months ago, and things have been nothing short of excellent so far. The amenities, cleanliness, and organization of this complex are all top-notch, but the main factor for Block C's success has been its leasing office team.

Jessica gave us our first tour of the place in March, and actually REMEMBERED us nine months later when we were finally ready to apply and move in! She is a gem. She is so knowledgable and patient, made us feel very recognized and welcomed, and facilitated a smooth move-in transition. Not many leasing companies seem to get this right - but Block C does: attention to detail and genuine care make ALL the difference to a resident! And we definitely felt that with Jessica.

More recently, many of our interactions have been with Sara, who has been nothing short of an angel. She is professional, she is knowledgable, and always willing to help. After we were approved, she helped us on move-in day and made sure we got everything we needed. But her care did NOT stop after that first day - she answered questions and coordinated repairs for weeks after that! She is so quick and responsive each and every time we correspond with her via email. She has helped us with storing our packages when we are out of town, accepted and coordinated larger deliveries for us, and paid rapt attention each time we had a maintenance issue. Each time there has been a maintenance request, she's made sure not only that it simply gets done, but also that it gets done to our satisfaction, and she doesn't just promise that it will and forget - she actually follows up and sees to it herself. You have no idea how much peace of mind that lends a resident, and I am thankful for it every day! Both Sara and Jessica go above and beyond by not only getting things done, but being SO cheerful and prompt with everything they do, and I marvel at their patience and energy!

We strongly believe that the best decision Block C's administration ever made was hiring Jessica and Sara. It takes great people to run a great office, and they have been amazing and deserve all the praise (and all the bonuses!) in the world. I know John has been a big part of this as well - he takes care and genuine interest in the operations of the entire community (which I bet is no easy job!) and is very attentive to our needs and our maintenance requests as well. The whole staff has an amazing attitude of service, pride in ownership + stewardship, and attention to detail, and I can tell he leads by example.

And it is not just the staff's kindness that makes this place so great - it is  genuinely a good place to live. The organization of the complex as a whole that makes me proud to live here. FOBs instead of keys? Genius. A remote door unlocking system for main entrances? Seamless (Why has the housing industry not applied this broadly yet??). A parcel pending package delivery system? What a life-saver. A mixed parking system? Best solution to the parking problem I've ever seen. Everything about Block C makes SENSE and is beautifully executed for the resident's ease and comfort. It truly is the future of the leasing experience. And on top of that, the security team and the maintenance team are effective and responsive. What more could you ask for?

As a young millennial, I've lived in my share of apartment complexes in and around southern California. At Block C, one of the main differences is that the whole staff makes us feel not like a burden (which is how I'm used to being treated by rental offices) but instead like appreciated members of their home and family! The complex itself is well-kept and well organized, and I couldn't be prouder to live here. Thank you!<//Review>

I got my Dave's style dog with a hot link. The hot dog was ok, nothing exceptional tasted like something I could make at home. Update:5->3.5star
10/9/19
Placed an online order for pickup since I have a 30min lunch. I arrived and checked in 5 minutes before the pickup time and the worker at the counter told me they didn't have an order for me, I showed them my online confirmation and they scrolled on their orders and finally found mine. <Rating>5</Rating>< review>
Good hot dogs. Note that the food stand on Milpas no longer exists and that Dave's has moved into this new location. I've had several of the hot dogs, and the Pizza Dog is the best and most memorable, featuring the hot dog covered with pizza sauce and parmesan cheese, and the bun closed over it all by an outside seal of melted and nearly-burnt mozzarella and pepperoni. Actually tastes very pizza like. Santa Barbara dog is good too -- reminds me of a "fancy" TJ Dog.<//review>

< Text>
I was driving back to LA from SF, decided on the scenic route (PCH) so a 6 hour trip turns into a 13 hour trip. By the time Santa Barbara comes into view, it already feels like I'm home.
I was looking for something delicious or at least different than a fast food joint, I found this little gem while loading gas for the last stretch of my trip.
It didn't seem exciting, I mean hot dogs, but at least they closed late and the reviews were pretty good.
Wow! This place will blow you away! Im not driving 100 miles just to eat there, but I'll definitely make a stop there if I'm on the area or passing by!
I ordered the Santa Barabara just to see what the locals like, it was so good I ordered a second one, El Ni√±o!
Both of them were delicious and surpassed my expectations.
The restroom is inside the kitchen, you gotta exit the restaurant and then they open a back door to let you in.<//Text>

I saw the reviews and I was excited! I love gourmet hotdog shops. I ordered the Santa Barbara Style with pastrami instead of bacon. They charged me two bucks extra for swapping then out. I also ordered a corn dog. I arrived to pick up before they called my name. I took food up to the car and begin to eat. The corn dog was tasty but definitely soggy. I took a bite out of my hot dog only to realize that there was no pastrami nor bacon. I went back inside and ask them to add some pastrami and throw some grilled jalapenos on it while they were at it. I told him to go ahead and leave the bacon on  since I had paid $2 extra anyway. I also ordered some pizza fries as well at that time. I got my new order and went back to the car to eat. This time there was about two small strips of pastrami oh, definitely not my $2 worth. The pizza fries word decent but soggy as well. I just want to reiterate that I'm literally parked outside of their door so I did not have to walk very far with my food. At that point, I did not want to go back in there with my mask and have to ask them to do anything else. This was a very frustrating experience considering they have such good reviews.</Review>

Oh my goodness I never knew hot dogs could have so many variations! I had the Santa Barbara style plus the El Nino and I still drool just thinking about them. They have this special cream sauce that's drizzled on a lot of their hotdogs and really takes flavor up a notch. And they have deep fried Oreos! So delicious.
